{"title_page": "Daqing re-education through labor camp", "text_new": "The '''Daqing re-education through labor camp''' is a [[re-education through labor]] camp located at 54 No. 22 Lane, Jingyi Street, [[Daqing]], [[China]].\n\nAccording to a [[United Nations]] report on Civil and Political Rights, in 2002 an inmate at the camp, He Huajiang, who was assigned to three years\u2019 re-education through labour for taking part in [[Falun Gong]] activities and disrupting public order, was reportedly{{By whom|date=May 2012}} [[tortured]] to death at the camp. According to reports,{{Which|date=May 2012}} there were [[strangulation]] marks around his throat and other signs of torture. Mr. He's body was allegedly taken to a different location for cremation.<ref>[http://www.unhchr.ch/Huridocda/Huridoca.nsf/0/77b55485d5d112bbc1256e67004eada3/$FILE/G0412275.doc CIVIL AND POLITICAL RIGHTS, INCLUDING THE QUESTIONS OF DISAPPEARANCES AND SUMMARY EXECUTIONS, Report of the Special Rapporteur, on extrajudicial, summary or arbitrary executions, by Asma Jahangir, pg 22]</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of re-education through labor camps in China]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://zsr.info/letters/Daqing01.htm Photo gallery of the camp]\n\n{{coord missing|Heilongjiang}}\n\n[[Category:Prisons in China]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Heilongjiang]]\n[[Category:Labour camps in China]]\n\n\n{{Heilongjiang-geo-stub}}\n", "text_old": "The '''Daqing re-education through labor camp''' is a [[re-education through labor]] camp located at 54 No. 22 Lane, Jingyi Street, [[Daqing]], [[China]].\n\nAccording to a [[United Nations]] report on Civil and Political Rights, in 2002 a inmate at the camp, He Huajiang, who was assigned to three years\u2019 re-education through labour for taking part in [[Falun Gong]] activities and disrupting public order, was reportedly{{By whom|date=May 2012}} [[tortured]] to death at the camp. According to reports,{{Which|date=May 2012}} there were [[strangulation]] marks around his throat and other signs of torture. Mr. He's body was allegedly taken to a different location for cremation.<ref>[http://www.unhchr.ch/Huridocda/Huridoca.nsf/0/77b55485d5d112bbc1256e67004eada3/$FILE/G0412275.doc CIVIL AND POLITICAL RIGHTS, INCLUDING THE QUESTIONS OF DISAPPEARANCES AND SUMMARY EXECUTIONS, Report of the Special Rapporteur, on extrajudicial, summary or arbitrary executions, by Asma Jahangir, pg 22]</ref>\n\n== See also ==\n* [[List of re-education through labor camps in China]]\n\n== References ==\n{{reflist}}\n\n== External links ==\n*[http://zsr.info/letters/Daqing01.htm Photo gallery of the camp]\n\n{{coord missing|Heilongjiang}}\n\n[[Category:Prisons in China]]\n[[Category:Buildings and structures in Heilongjiang]]\n[[Category:Labour camps in China]]\n\n\n{{Heilongjiang-geo-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: a inmate \u2192 an inmate", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Daqing_re-education_through_labor_camp"}
{"title_page": "NFL GameDay 2002", "text_new": "{{short description|2001 PS1 and PS2 video game}}\n{{Infobox VG\n|title = NFL GameDay 2002\n|image = \n|caption =\n|developer = [[989 Studios|989 Sports]] <small>(PS)</small><br />[[Red Zone Interactive]] <small>(PS2)</small>\n|publisher = [[Sony Interactive Entertainment|Sony Computer Entertainment America]]\n|designer =\n|series = ''[[NFL GameDay (video game series)|NFL GameDay]]''\n|engine =\n|released = '''PlayStation'''<br />{{vgrelease|NA|August 7, 2001<ref name=\"NFL_2002_release\"/>}}'''PlayStation 2'''<br />{{vgrelease|NA|December 4, 2001<ref name=\"NFL_2002_PS2_release\"/>}}\n|genre = Sports\n|modes = [[Single-player video game|Single-player]], [[Multiplayer video game|multiplayer]]\n|platforms = [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]], [[PlayStation 2]]\n}}\n\n'''''NFL GameDay 2002''''' is the seventh video game in the ''[[NFL GameDay (video game series)|NFL GameDay]]'' series. It was developed by [[989 Studios|989 Sports]] and [[Red Zone Interactive]] and published [[Sony Interactive Entertainment|Sony Computer Entertainment America]] for the [[PlayStation (console)|PlayStation]] and the [[PlayStation 2]] in 2001.<ref name=\"NFL_2002_PS2_release\">{{cite web |title=All New and Redesigned NFL GameDay(TM) 2002 Now Available for Gridiron Action On the PlayStation(R)2 Computer Entertainment System |url=http://www.thefreelibrary.com/All+New+and+Redesigned+NFL+GameDay%28TM%29+2002+Now+Available+for...-a080595728 |website=PR Newswire |publisher=Cision |date=December 4, 2001 |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20121024025410/http://www.thefreelibrary.com/All+New+and+Redesigned+NFL+GameDay(TM)+2002+Now+Available+for...-a080595728 |archivedate=October 24, 2012 |url-status=dead |accessdate=April 9, 2020}}</ref> On the cover is [[Donovan McNabb]].<ref name=\"NFL_2002_PS2_release\"/><ref name=\"NFL_2002_release\">{{cite web |title=NFL GameDay(TM) 2002 Takes to the Gridiron for Another PlayStation(R) Season. |url=http: