{"title_page": "Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez", "text_new": "{{Infobox stadium\n| stadium_name      = Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez\n| nickname          = \n| image             = Estadio Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px\n| fullname          = Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez\n| location          = [[Quillota]], [[Chile]] \n| coordinates       = \n| broke_ground      =\n| built             = 2010\n| opened            = September 15, 2010\n| renovated         = \n| expanded          = \n| closed            = \n| demolished        = \n| owner             = [[Quillota|Municipality of Quillota]]\n| operator          = \n| surface           = \n| construction_cost = \n| architect         =\n| structural engineer =\n| services engineer =\n| general_contractor=\n| project_manager   =\n| main_contractors  = \n| former_names      = \n| tenants           = [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]]\n| seating_capacity  = 7,680\n| dimensions        =\n}}\n\n'''Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Quillota]], [[Chile]].  It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, and is the home stadium of [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]] which currently plays at the [[Primera B de Chile|second tier]] of the Chilean league system.  The stadium holds 7,680 spectators. The stadium was opened on September 15, 2010 in a [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]] against [[C.D. Universidad de Concepcion|Universidad de Concepcion]], match which ended in a final 1-0 for the home team.\n\n==See also==\n[[List of football stadiums in Chile]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130117012801/http://www.worldstadiums.com/south_america/countries/chile.shtml Stadium information]\n\n{{coord|32.8876|S|71.252|W|source:kolossus-eswiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Primera Divisi\u00f3n de Chile Venues}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Estadio Municipal Lucio Farina Fernandez}}\n[[Category:Football venues in Chile|Municipal Lucio Farina Fernandez]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in Valpara\u00edso Region]]\n\n\n{{Chile-sports-venue-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox stadium\n| stadium_name      = Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez\n| nickname          = \n| image             = Estadio Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez.jpg\n| image_size        = 250px\n| fullname          = Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez\n| location          = [[Quillota]], [[Chile]] \n| coordinates       = \n| broke_ground      =\n| built             = 2010\n| opened            = September 15, 2010\n| renovated         = \n| expanded          = \n| closed            = \n| demolished        = \n| owner             = [[Quillota|Municipality of Quillota]]\n| operator          = \n| surface           = \n| construction_cost = \n| architect         =\n| structural engineer =\n| services engineer =\n| general_contractor=\n| project_manager   =\n| main_contractors  = \n| former_names      = \n| tenants           = [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]]\n| seating_capacity  = 7,680\n| dimensions        =\n}}\n\n'''Estadio Municipal Lucio Fari\u00f1a Fern\u00e1ndez''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Quillota]], [[Chile]].  It is currently used mostly for [[football (soccer)|football]] matches, and is the home stadium of [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]] which currently plays at the [[Primera B de Chile|second tier]] of the chilean league system.  The stadium holds 7,680 spectators. The stadium was opened on September 15, 2010 in a [[San Luis de Quillota|San Luis]] against [[C.D. Universidad de Concepcion|Universidad de Concepcion]], match which ended in a final 1-0 for the home team.\n\n==See also==\n[[List of football stadiums in Chile]]\n\n==External links==\n*[https://web.archive.org/web/20130117012801/http://www.worldstadiums.com/south_america/countries/chile.shtml Stadium information]\n\n{{coord|32.8876|S|71.252|W|source:kolossus-eswiki|display=title}}\n\n{{Primera Divisi\u00f3n de Chile Venues}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Estadio Municipal Lucio Farina Fernandez}}\n[[Category:Football venues in Chile|Municipal Lucio Farina Fernandez]]\n[[Category:Sports venues in Valpara\u00edso Region]]\n\n\n{{Chile-sports-venue-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "\u2192\u200etop:Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: chilean \u2192 Chilean", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Estadio_Municipal_Lucio_Fari%C3%B1a_Fern%C3%A1ndez"}
{"title_page": "M\u011bstsk\u00fd fotbalov\u00fd stadion Miroslava Valenty", "text_new": "{{Infobox stadium\n| stadium_name      = M\u011bstsk\u00fd fotbalov\u00fd stadion Miroslava Valenty\n| nickname          =\n| image             = Stadion Miroslava Valenty.png\n| fullname          =\n| location          = [[Uhersk\u00e9 Hradi\u0161t\u011b]], [[Czech Republic]]\n| coordinates       = {{Coord|49|03|56.00|N|17|28|17.26|E|display=inline,title|region:CZ_type:landmark}}\n| broke_ground      =\n| built             =\n| opened            = 2003\n| renovated         =\n| expanded          =\n| closed            =\n| demolished        =\n| owner             = [[Uhersk\u00e9 Hradi\u0161t\u011b|The City of Uhersk\u00e9 Hradi\u0161t\u011b]]\n| operator          =\n| surface           =\n| construction_cost = 251 million [[Czech koruna|koruna]]\n| architect         =\n| structural engineer =\n| services engineer =\n| general_contractor=\n| project_manager   =\n| main_contractors  =\n| former_names      =\n| tenants           = [[1. FC Slov\u00e1cko]] (2003-present)<br>[[Czech Republic national football team]] (selected matches)\n| seating_capacity  = 8,121\n| dimensions        = 105x68m\n}}\n\n'''M\u011bstsk\u00fd fotbalov\u00fd stadion Miroslava Valenty''' is a multi-use [[stadium]] in [[Uhersk\u00e9 Hradi\u0161t\u011b]], [[Czech Republic]]. It is used mostly for [[association football|football]] matches and is the home ground of [[1. FC Slov\u00e1cko]]. The stadium has an all-seated capacity of 8,121 people.\n\nThe first match to take place at the stadium was a friendly match on 12 October 2003, with Slov\u00e1cko hosting German side [[Borussia M\u00f6nchengladbach]]. The hosts won 3\u20132.<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/synot-otevrel-stadion-vyhrou-nad-nemci-d9w-/fotbal.aspx?c=A031012_202853_fotbal_ber|title=Synot otev\u0159el stadion v\u00fdhrou nad N\u011bmci |language=Czech |publisher=idnes.cz |date=12 October 2003 |accessdate=30 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nDuring the [[2003\u201304 Gambrinus liga]], Synot played their home games for the first part of the season at Brno and Drnovice. Their first home league match at the stadium was on 18 October 2003 against [[SK Sigma Olomouc|Olomouc]].<ref>{{cite news |url=http://fotbal.idnes.cz/synot-otevre-areal-v-uherskem-hradisti-d9e-/fotbal.aspx?c=A031007_181038_fotbal_ruz|title=Synot otev\u0159e are\u00e1l v Uhersk\u00e9m Hradi\u0161ti |language=Czech |publisher=idnes.cz |date=7 October 2003 |accessdate=30 September 2011}}</ref>\n\nIn August 2009, it was announced that the stadium would be renamed ''M\u011bstsk\u00fd fotbalov\u00fd stadion Miroslava Valenty'' after the 2008 death of benefactor Miroslav Valenta.\n\n\nMulticipal-Stadium-Uherske Hradiste,(CZE),in the Name of Miroslav Valenta,(translation):/(eng)\n\nAddress: Ulica Stonky 566\n        \n        CZ -68 601 Uherske Hradiste \n        CZECH REPUBLIC\n\n        (Distrikt: Maratice,Rybarny,)\n\nDrive :  E50, DK55,DK 497,\n\n <ref>{{cite news |url=http://slovacky.denik.cz/zpravy_region/miroslav-valenta-stadion-uherske-hradiste-20090825.html|title=Hradi\u0161\u0165sk\u00fd stadion ponese Valentovo jm\u00e9no |language=Czech |publisher=denik.cz |date=25 August 2009 |accessdate=30 September 2011}}</ref>\n\n== International matches ==\nM\u011bstsk\u00fd fotbalov\u00fd stadion Miroslava Valenty has hosted three full internationals of the [[Czech national football team|Czech national team]].\n\n----\n{{footballbox\n|date = 16 August 2006\n|team1 = {{fb-rt|CZE}}\n|score = 1&ndash;3\n|report= [https://web.archive.org/web/20090211212456/http://www.fotbal.cz/c/nat/AM/2006/match8.asp (Report)]\n|team2 = {{fb|SER}}\n|goals1=[[Ji\u0159\u00ed \u0160tajner|\u0160tajner]] {{goal|3}}\n|goals2=[[Danko Lazovi\u0107|Lazovi\u0107]] {{goal|41}}<br />[[Marko Panteli\u0107|Panteli\u0107]] {{goal|54}}<br />[[Aleksandar Tri\u0161ovi\u0107|Tri\u0161ovi\u0107]] {{goal|70}}\n|stadium = [[Exhibition game|International Friendly]] | |attendance=8,047 |