{"title_page": "Colegio Altamira International School", "text_new": "{{Primary sources|date=April 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name = Altamira International School\n| image = \n| established = 1992 \n| type = [[Private school|Private]]\n| principal = Priscilla Ruiz de Vergara\n| location = Km 10 Autopista a Puerto Colombia<br />[[Barranquilla, Colombia]]\n| website = http://www.altamira.edu.co\n}}\n\nThe '''Altamira International School''', located in [[Barranquilla]], Colombia, is a [[Private school|private]], [[Nonsectarian|non-sectarian]], non-profit coeducational U.S. college preparatory school open to the enrollment of Colombians, North Americans, and children of other countries.  The school intends to meet the needs of the community by providing an education based on the best theories and practices of Colombia and the United States. The basic language of instruction is English, and the school staff, whenever possible, is completely bilingual and almost professionally qualified in their areas of instruction, the majority of them local hires. At the present time, the school offers an educational program from [[Pre-kindergarten|Pre-K]] through 12th grade for the 2005\u20132006 school year.  The school is accredited by the [[Ministry of National Education (Colombia)|Colombian Ministry of Education]] and an invitational member of the Tri-Association of Schools of Central America, Colombia-Caribbean and Mexico.\n\n<br />\n\n== Extracurricular Activities ==\nAltamira offer extracurricular activities such as STEM Club, Theatre, Taekwondo, Soccer, Volleyball, Basketball, Chess, Yoga, Art, Music, Lego Mindstorm amongst others. Altamira's objective is to complement the integral training that students receive, promoting alternative spaces, where students can pursue their passions, develop new skills, collaborate and have fun. These activities allow students to explore physical, creative, social, political and career interests with like-minded peers. They get to collaborate, communicate, be creative and develop critical thinking skills that allow them to better perform in the Twenty First Century.\n\n<br />\n== Accreditation ==\nThe school is accredited by the Colombian [http://www.mineducacion.gov.co Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n Nacional]\nand '''SACS CASI'''.\n\n<br />\n== Facilities ==\n* '''Antonio Ruiz Angulo Coliseum''' opened in May 2009 and is a multipurpose center used for playing different sports as well as the main venue where academic celebrations take place.\n*'''Cafetorium''' Opened in 2019 and is a cafeteria that can be switched to an Auditorium.\n\n<br />\n== See slso ==\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/AIS-DRESS-CODE.pdf AIS Dress Code]\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/house-system/ AIS House System]\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/about-ais/our-school/ AIS Vision and mission statement]\n\n<br />\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{portal|Schools}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1992]]\n[[Category:International schools in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Schools in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Association of American Schools in South America]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in Colombia]]\n\n\n{{Colombia-school-stub}}\n", "text_old": "{{Primary sources|date=April 2009}}\n\n{{Infobox school\n| name = Altamira International School\n| image = \n| established = 1992 \n| type = [[Private school|Private]]\n| principal = Priscilla Ruiz de Vergara\n| location = Km 10 Autopista a Puerto Colombia<br />[[Barranquilla, Colombia]]\n| website = http://www.altamira.edu.co\n}}\n\nThe '''Altamira International School''', located in [[Barranquilla]], Colombia, is a [[Private school|private]], [[Nonsectarian|non-sectarian]], non-profit coeducational U.S. college preparatory school open to the enrollment of Colombians, North Americans, and children of other countries.  The school intends to meet the needs of the community by providing an education based on the best theories and practices of Colombia and the United States. The basic language of instruction is English, and the school staff, whenever possible, is completely bilingual and almost professionally qualified in their areas of instruction, the majority of them local hires. At the present time, the school offers an educational program from [[Pre-kindergarten|Pre-K]] through 12th grade for the 2005-2006 school year.  The school is accredited by the [[Ministry of National Education (Colombia)|Colombian Ministry of Education]] and an invitational member of the Tri-Association of Schools of Central America, Colombia-Caribbean and Mexico.\n\n<br />\n\n== Extracurricular Activities ==\nAltamira offer extracurricular activities such as STEM Club, Theatre, Taekwondo, Soccer, Volleyball, Basketball, Chess, Yoga, Art, Music, Lego Mindstorm amongst others. Altamira's objective is to complement the integral training that students receive, promoting alternative spaces, where students can pursue their passions, develop new skills, collaborate and have fun. These activities allow students to explore physical, creative, social, political and career interests with like-minded peers. They get to collaborate, communicate, be creative and develop critical thinking skills that allow them to better perform in the Twenty First Century.\n\n<br />\n== Accreditation ==\nThe school is accredited by the Colombian [http://www.mineducacion.gov.co Ministerio de Educaci\u00f3n Nacional]\nand '''SACS CASI'''.\n\n<br />\n== Facilities ==\n* '''Antonio Ruiz Angulo Coliseum''' opened in May 2009 and is a multipurpose center used for playing different sports as well as the main venue where academic celebrations take place.\n*'''Cafetorium''' Opened in 2019 and is a cafeteria that can be switched to a Auditorium.\n\n<br />\n== See slso ==\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/wp-content/uploads/2019/09/AIS-DRESS-CODE.pdf AIS Dress Code]\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/house-system/ AIS House System]\n\n* [https://altamira.edu.co/about-ais/our-school/ AIS Vision and mission statement]\n\n<br />\n==References==\n{{reflist}}\n\n{{portal|Schools}}\n\n[[Category:Educational institutions established in 1992]]\n[[Category:International schools in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Schools in Colombia]]\n[[Category:Association of American Schools in South America]]\n[[Category:1992 establishments in Colombia]]\n\n\n{{Colombia-school-stub}}\n", "name_user": "Iridescent", "label": "safe", "comment": "Cleanup andtypo fixing,typo(s) fixed: 2005-2006 \u2192 2005\u20132006, a Auditorium. \u2192 an Auditorium.", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Colegio_Altamira_International_School"}
{"title_page": "Animation Domination", "text_new": "{{for|the former sister programming block on [[FXX]]|Animation Domination High-Def}}\n{{Infobox programming block\n| name                   = Animation Domination\n| image                  = File:AnimationDomination2019.jpg\n| channel                = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| country                = United States\n| format                 = [[Adult animation]]<br>[[Comedy]]<br>[[Sitcom]]\n| premiered              = '''Original run:''' {{Start date and age|2005|05|01}}<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=http://tviv.org/Animation_Domination|title=Animation Domination|work=tviv.org}}</ref><br />'''Second run:''' {{Start date|2019|09|29}}<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36KEvxAL6Ac|title=Animation Domination &#124; PROMO &#124; Returns This Fall! (+ Bless The Hearts Promo)|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n| closed                 ='''Original run:''' {{End date|2014|09|21}}\n| runtime                = \n| caption                = Logo for the 2019 incarnation\n| website                = https://www.fox.com/animation-domination/\n| type                   = Sunday night animation block \n}}\n\n'''Animation Domination''' is an [[television animation|animated]] [[block programming|programming block]] which has aired in two iterations on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] broadcast network, featuring a lineup solely made up of [[adult animation]] produced by [[Walt Disney Television]]'s [[20th Century Fox Television]] division carried as a majority of, or the whole of, the network's Sunday evening schedule (outside of [[Fox Sports (United States)|sports pre-emptions]] and early hour programming [[burning off|burn offs]]).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=35}}</ref>\n\nIt originally ran from May 1, 2005, until September 21, 2014, before returning on September 29, 2019.<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/06/24/fox-premiere-dates-fall-2019-empire-final-season/|title=Fox Fall Premiere Dates: Empire's Final Season, XL Masked Singer and More|first1=Michael|last1=Ausiello|first2=Michael|last2=Ausiello|date=June 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Original run===\nAnimation Domination debuted on Fox on May 1, 2005, in time for the last [[sweeps]] period of the [[2004\u201305 United States network television schedule|2004\u201305 television season]]. The first program to originate on the block was ''[[American Dad!]]'', although its \"[[Pilot (American Dad!)|pilot]]\" aired as a [[Super Bowl XXXIX|Super Bowl]] [[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|lead-out program]] on February 6, 2005. Rounding out the Animation Domination lineup alongside ''American Dad!'' were ''[[The Simpsons]]'' (the longest-running cartoon on Fox and the network's first primetime animated series, which predated the lineup by 16 years), ''[[King of the Hill]]'' (which predated the lineup by eight years) and ''[[Family Guy]]'' (which predated the lineup by six years, and was revived as a series three years after its 2002 cancellation as a result of newfound popularity through reruns on [[Cartoon Network]]'s [[Adult Swim]] lineup and sales of the first, second, and third-season episodes on DVD).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://animatedtv.about.com/od/foxnetwork/a/may2005fox.htm|title=New Episodes on FOX's Animation Domination|author=Nancy Basile|work=About.com Entertainment|access-date=2012-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513061053/http://animatedtv.about.com/od/foxnetwork/a/may2005fox.htm|archive-date=2013-05-13|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite web|url=http://animatedtv.about.com/b/2005/04/20/foxs-animation-domination-for-may.htm|title=New Episodes on FOX's Animation Domination|author=Nancy Basile|work=About.com Entertainment|access-date=2012-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080425025132/http://animatedtv.about.com/b/2005/04/20/foxs-animation-domination-for-may.htm|archive-date=2008-04-25|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in the [[2014\u201315 United States network television schedule|fall of 2014]], the Animation Domination block was replaced by the ''Sunday Funday'' block, with the addition of live-action comedies ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]'' (which moved to Sunday night for its second season), freshman series ''[[Mulaney]]'' (which was canceled in early 2015), and, as of March 2015, the [[Will Forte]] sitcom, ''[[The Last Man on Earth (TV series)|The Last Man on Earth]]''. This marks the first time that the network has regularly aired live-action comedies on Sundays (outside of [[burning off|burn-offs]] of failed weeknight series) since 2005.\n\n===Return===\nThe block returned on September 29, 2019, with previous ''AD'' series ''[[The Simpsons]]'', ''[[Bob's Burgers]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', and the new series ''[[Bless the Harts]]''.<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\"/>\n\n==Programming==\n===Current programming===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Premiere date !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Note !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Time slot\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Simpsons]]'' || rowspan=2| {{dts|2005|5|01}} || rowspan=\"3\" | Previously aired as part of [[Fox Sunday Night]]/[[Sunday Funday]] || 8:00PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Family Guy]]''  || 9:30PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Bob's Burgers]]''|| {{dts|2011|1|9}} || 9:00PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Bless the Harts]]'' || {{dts|2019|9|29}} || || N/A\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Duncanville (TV series)|Duncanville]]'' || {{dts|2020|02|16}} || Second season will debut in the [[2021-22 United States network television schedule|2021-22 television season]] || 8:30PM\n|}\n\n===Upcoming programming===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Premiere date !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Note !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Time slot\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Great North]]'' || TBA || || TBA\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Housebroken (TV series)|Housebroken]]'' || TBA || First \"Animation Domination\" animated series to not be produced by 20th Century Fox Television || TBA\n|-\n|}\n\n===Former programming===\n<!-- For last aired date, only include the last time it aired on the block, not the day the last episode aired -->\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | First aired !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Last aired !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Note\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[King of the Hill]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |May 1, 2005\n|September 13, 2009\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[American Dad!]]''\n|September 21, 2014\n|Moved to TBS\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Sit Down, Shut Up (2009 TV series)|Sit Down, Shut Up]]''\n|April 19, 2009\n|May 10, 2009\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Cleveland Show]]''\n|September 27, 2009\n|July 14, 2013<!--This is the last aired, not the series finale date, leave as is according to table-->\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Allen Gregory]]''\n|October 30, 2011\n|December 18, 2011\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Napoleon Dynamite (TV series)|Napoleon Dynamite]]''\n|January 15, 2012\n|March 4, 2012\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Axe Cop (TV series)|Axe Cop]]''\n| colspan=\"2\" rowspan=\"2\" |July 21, 2013\n| rowspan=\"2\" |Special preview/Aired on ADHD\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[High School USA!]]''\n|- \n|}\n\n== Current line-up ==\n\n===2019/20===\n{| class=\"wikitable\" style=\"width:100%;margin-right:0;text-align:center\"\n|-\n! colspan=\"2\" style=\"width:11.5%;\"|Network\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|7:00 PM\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|7:30 PM\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|8:00 PM\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|8:30 PM\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|9:00 PM\n! style=\"width:11.5%;\"|9:30 PM\n|-\n! rowspan=\"7\" |[[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n! Fall\n| style=\"background:cyan\"| ''[[Fox NFL]]''\n| The OT/Fox Encores\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''[[The Simpsons]]''<ref name=\"Simpsons\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/simpsons/listings/|'The Simpsons' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n| ''[[Bless the Harts]]''\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''[[Bob's Burgers]]''\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''[[Family Guy]]''<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/family-guy/listings/|title='Family Guy' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|-\n! Winter\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''The Simpsons'' {{small|(R)}}<ref name=\"Simpsons\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/simpsons/listings/|'The Simpsons' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"3\"|''Bob's Burgers'' {{small|(R)}}<ref name=\"Bob\">{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/bobs-burgers/listings/|title='Bob's Burgers' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n| rowspan=\"2\"|''[[Duncanville (TV series)|Duncanville]]''\n|-\n! style=\"background:#FFFFA3;\"|Spring\n|-\n! Summer\n| ''The Simpsons'' {{small|(R)}}<ref name=\"Simpsons\"/>\n| ''Bless the Harts'' {{small|(R)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/bless-the-harts/listings/|title='Bless the Harts' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n| ''Bob's Burgers'' {{small|(R)}}<ref name=\"Bob\"/>\n| ''Family Guy'' {{small|(R)}}<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.thefutoncritic.com/showatch/family-guy/listings/|title='Family Guy' listings|accessdate=10 April 2020}}</ref>\n|}\n\n==International versions==\nInternational Fox-branded networks, such as Australia's [[Fox8]], and the Fox cable networks in [[Fox (Italy)|Italy]], [[Fox (Bulgaria)|Bulgaria]] and [[Fox (Spain)|Spain]] carry local versions of the block [[Dub localization|dubbed]] into local languages.\n\nIn New Zealand, [[Four (New Zealand)|FOUR]] ras a two-hour animated block on Thursday nights named \"Animation Station\" that was, for the most part, a domestic version of Animation Domination. Fox shows that were included in the Animation Station lineup are ''American Dad!'', ''Bob's Burgers'' and ''Family Guy''. Former Animation Domination shows have also been featured in this block, namely ''The Cleveland Show'' and ''King of the Hill'', as well as former Fox cartoon ''[[Futurama]]''. With the closure of FOUR in 2016, the block was quietly ended.\n\nIn Canada, the block aired on the [[Global Television Network]], which branded the lineup as \"Animation Rules\" with [[simultaneous substitution]]s for Canadian advertising. Throughout its run it was always followed by the drama ''[[Brothers and Sisters (2006 TV series)|Brothers and Sisters]]'', which was a simsub of the ABC broadcast, except that from 2005 to 2006, it was followed by ''[[Crossing Jordan]]'', which was a simsub of the NBC broadcast, because neither ''Brothers and Sisters'' was created, nor it was ready yet, And from 2011 To the Original Block's End In 2014, ''[[The Good Wife]]'' Followed It, which Was a Simsub of the CBS broadcast, Because ''Brothers and Sisters'' Finished airing its run.\n\nAs for the 2019 incarnation, in Canada, it was aired on [[Citytv]], and it was followed by reruns of ''[[Mom (TV series)|Mom]]''.\n\n==Animation Domination High-Def==\n<!-- Please do not add or change to the 'closed' entry until Animation Domination Hi-Def official ceases broadcasting on FOX. --->\n{{Main|Animation Domination High-Def}}\nOn January 8, 2013, Fox announced that it would launch an [[adult animation]] spin-off to its Sunday evening block called '''Animation Domination High-Definition'''.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z2z2z345z3z8&ID=12360|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20130313090726/http://www.foxflash.com/div.php/main/page?aID=1z2z2z345z3z8&ID=12360|title=FOX FLASH - FOX PRIMETIME|archivedate=13 March 2013|work=foxflash.com}}</ref> It originally broadcast on Saturday evenings for 90 minutes from 11:00&nbsp;p.m. to 12:30&nbsp;a.m. local time in most markets. It was later reduced to 11:00&nbsp;p.m. to 12:00&nbsp;a.m. on September 7, 2013, with the 12:00&nbsp;a.m. half-hour being given back to its [[owned-and-operated station]]s and [[network affiliate|affiliate]]s to carry other programming. Some of its affiliates delayed the block by 30 minutes to an hour to run late evening newscasts (sports overruns occasionally caused further delays).\n\nThe last edition of ''ADHD'' on Fox aired on March 5, 2016, with the new [[Lonely Island]] [[sketch comedy]] series ''[[Party Over Here]]'' to premiere in the slot on March 12.\n\n==See also==\n* [[List of programs broadcast by Fox]]\n* [[Animation on Fox]]\n* [[Fox Sunday Night]]\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{official site}}\n\n{{Navboxes|list1=\n{{Fox Animation}}\n{{FOXNetwork Shows (current and upcoming)}}\n{{The Simpsons}}\n{{Family Guy}}\n{{American Dad!}}\n{{The Cleveland Show}}\n{{Bob's Burgers}}\n{{King of the Hill}}\n{{Napoleon Dynamite}}\n}}\n{{Portal bar|Animation|Comedy|Television|United States|The Simpsons}}\n\n[[Category:Television programming blocks in the United States]]\n[[Category:Fox Broadcasting Company]]\n[[Category:2005 introductions]]\n", "text_old": "{{for|the former sister programming block on [[FXX]]|Animation Domination High-Def}}\n{{Infobox programming block\n| name                   = Animation Domination\n| image                  = File:AnimationDomination2019.jpg\n| channel                = [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]]\n| country                = United States\n| format                 = [[Adult animation]]<br>[[Comedy]]<br>[[Sitcom]]\n| premiered              = '''Original run:''' {{Start date and age|2005|05|01}}<ref name=autogenerated2>{{cite web|url=http://tviv.org/Animation_Domination|title=Animation Domination|work=tviv.org}}</ref><br />'''Second run:''' {{Start date|2019|09|29}}<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\">{{Cite web|url=https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=36KEvxAL6Ac|title=Animation Domination &#124; PROMO &#124; Returns This Fall! (+ Bless The Hearts Promo)|via=www.youtube.com}}</ref>\n| closed                 ='''Original run:''' {{End date|2014|09|21}}\n| runtime                = \n| caption                = Logo for the 2019 incarnation\n| website                = https://www.fox.com/animation-domination/\n| type                   = Sunday night animation block \n}}\n\n'''Animation Domination''' is an [[television animation|animated]] [[block programming|programming block]] which has aired in two iterations on the [[Fox Broadcasting Company|Fox]] broadcast network, featuring a lineup solely made up of [[adult animation]] produced by [[Walt Disney Television]]'s [[20th Century Fox Television]] division carried as a majority of, or the whole of, the network's Sunday evening schedule (outside of [[Fox Sports (United States)|sports pre-emptions]] and early hour programming [[burning off|burn offs]]).<ref>{{cite book |last1=Perlmutter |first1=David |title=The Encyclopedia of American Animated Television Shows |date=2018 |publisher=Rowman & Littlefield |isbn=978-1538103739 |page=35}}</ref>\n\nIt originally ran from May 1, 2005, until September 21, 2014, before returning on September 29, 2019.<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\"/><ref>{{Cite web|url=https://tvline.com/2019/06/24/fox-premiere-dates-fall-2019-empire-final-season/|title=Fox Fall Premiere Dates: Empire's Final Season, XL Masked Singer and More|first1=Michael|last1=Ausiello|first2=Michael|last2=Ausiello|date=June 24, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==History==\n===Original run===\nAnimation Domination debuted on Fox on May 1, 2005, in time for the last [[sweeps]] period of the [[2004\u201305 United States network television schedule|2004\u201305 television season]]. The first program to originate on the block was ''[[American Dad!]]'', although its \"[[Pilot (American Dad!)|pilot]]\" aired as a [[Super Bowl XXXIX|Super Bowl]] [[List of Super Bowl lead-out programs|lead-out program]] on February 6, 2005. Rounding out the Animation Domination lineup alongside ''American Dad!'' were ''[[The Simpsons]]'' (the longest-running cartoon on Fox and the network's first primetime animated series, which predated the lineup by 16 years), ''[[King of the Hill]]'' (which predated the lineup by eight years) and ''[[Family Guy]]'' (which predated the lineup by six years, and was revived as a series three years after its 2002 cancellation as a result of newfound popularity through reruns on [[Cartoon Network]]'s [[Adult Swim]] lineup and sales of the first, second, and third-season episodes on DVD).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://animatedtv.about.com/od/foxnetwork/a/may2005fox.htm|title=New Episodes on FOX's Animation Domination|author=Nancy Basile|work=About.com Entertainment|access-date=2012-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20130513061053/http://animatedtv.about.com/od/foxnetwork/a/may2005fox.htm|archive-date=2013-05-13|url-status=dead}}</ref><ref name=autogenerated4>{{cite web|url=http://animatedtv.about.com/b/2005/04/20/foxs-animation-domination-for-may.htm|title=New Episodes on FOX's Animation Domination|author=Nancy Basile|work=About.com Entertainment|access-date=2012-01-16|archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080425025132/http://animatedtv.about.com/b/2005/04/20/foxs-animation-domination-for-may.htm|archive-date=2008-04-25|url-status=dead}}</ref>\n\nBeginning in the [[2014\u201315 United States network television schedule|fall of 2014]], the Animation Domination block was replaced by the ''Sunday Funday'' block, with the addition of live-action comedies ''[[Brooklyn Nine-Nine]]'' (which moved to Sunday night for its second season), freshman series ''[[Mulaney]]'' (which was canceled in early 2015), and, as of March 2015, the [[Will Forte]] sitcom, ''[[The Last Man on Earth (TV series)|The Last Man on Earth]]''. This marks the first time that the network has regularly aired live-action comedies on Sundays (outside of [[burning off|burn-offs]] of failed weeknight series) since 2005.\n\n===Return===\nThe block returned on September 29, 2019, with previous ''AD'' series ''[[The Simpsons]]'', ''[[Bob's Burgers]]'', ''[[Family Guy]]'', and the new series ''[[Bless the Harts]]''.<ref name=\"AnimationDominationReturns\"/>\n\n==Programming==\n===Current programming===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Premiere date !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Note !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Time slot\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Simpsons]]'' || rowspan=2| {{dts|2005|5|01}} || rowspan=\"3\" | Previously aired as part of [[Fox Sunday Night]]/[[Sunday Funday]] || 8:00PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Family Guy]]''  || 9:30PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Bob's Burgers]]''|| {{dts|2011|1|9}} || 9:00PM\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Bless the Harts]]'' || {{dts|2019|9|29}} || || N/A\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Duncanville (TV series)|Duncanville]]'' || {{dts|2020|02|16}} || Second season will debut in the [[2021-22 United States network television schedule|2021-22 television season]] || 8:30PM\n|}\n\n===Upcoming programming===\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Premiere date !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Note !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Time slot\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Great North]]'' || TBA || || TBA\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Housebroken (TV series)|Housebroken]]'' || TBA || First \"Animation Domination\" animated series to not be produced by 20th Century Fox Television || TBA\n|-\n|}\n\n===Former programming===\n<!-- For last aired date, only include the last time it aired on the block, not the day the last episode aired -->\n{| class=\"wikitable plainrowheaders sortable\" style=\"width:85%;text-align:center;\"\n! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:30%;\" | Title !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | First aired !! scope=\"col\" style=\"width:14%;\" | Last aired !! class=\"unsortable\" style=\"width:5%;\" | Note\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[King of the Hill]]''\n| rowspan=\"2\" |May 1, 2005\n|September 13, 2009\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[American Dad!]]''\n|September 21, 2014\n|Moved to TBS\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Sit Down, Shut Up (2009 TV series)|Sit Down, Shut Up]]''\n|April 19, 2009\n|May 10, 2009\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[The Cleveland Show]]''\n|September 27, 2009\n|July 14, 2013<!--This is the last aired, not the series finale date, leave as is according to table-->\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Allen Gregory]]''\n|October 30, 2011\n|December 18, 2011\n|\n|-\n| scope=\"row\" style=\"text-align:left;\" | ''[[Napoleon Dynamite (TV series)|Napoleon Dynamite]]''\n|January 15, 2012\n|March 4, 2012\n|